WARNING: STORY CONTAINS GRAPHIC DETAILS A 16-year-old teenager is expected to appear in the Pampierstad Magistrate’s Court in the Northern Cape on a charge of murder. It’s alleged the 16-year-old murdered his 17-year-old peer, beheaded him and dumped his body in a trench. The horrific incident has left the community in shock and disbelief. Seventeen-year old Lucky Taole was last seen on Saturday with his two peers. The next morning his decapitated body was discovered by a passerby. His family says his neck is still missing.